HEADWORD: hirudinean
<hw>hirudinean</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any of a number of carnivorous or
bloodsucking aquatic or terrestrial worms typically having a sucker at
each end.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> leech, bloodsucker.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

